
Overview of noun charity

The noun charity has 5 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (2) charity -- (a foundation created to promote the public good (not for assistance to any particular individuals))
2. (1) charity, brotherly love -- (a kindly and lenient attitude toward people)
3. (1) charity -- (an activity or gift that benefits the public at large)
4. Jacob's ladder, Greek valerian, charity, Polemonium caeruleum, Polemonium van-bruntiae, Polymonium caeruleum van-bruntiae -- (pinnate-leaved European perennial having bright blue or white flowers)
5. charity -- (an institution set up to provide help to the needy)
